THE COURT FINDS:
1.  The inmate has not previously petitioned for sentence adjustment under 973.195, Wis. Stats.  
2.  The inmate has not previously petitioned for sentence adjustment within one year of filing this petition under 973.198, Wis. Stats. for this sentence.  
3.  The inmate is not serving a sentence for a Class A or Class B felony.
4.  The inmate has served the applicable percentage of his/her confinement in prison. 
5.  District Attorney notification requirements have been met.
6.  Victim notification requirements, if any, have been met.
THE COURT ORDERS the petition for sentence adjustment is denied because:  it is not in the public interest
